# API & State

Source of truth: @ai/rules/projects/fin-app-mobile/state-management.md

## Quick Rules

- Never call `axios` directly outside `src/shared/api/`
- All HTTP in `src/shared/api/*.ts` — export functions, not instance
- Use `apiClient` from `src/shared/api/base.ts` — never create new axios instances
- Axios instance: `baseURL` from `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`, auth header, timeout
- React Query for ALL server state (lists, detail, pagination, mutations)
- Every mutation MUST call `queryClient.invalidateQueries()` after success — never leave stale cache
- Query keys: typed constants only — `QUERY_KEYS.wallets.all`, not raw `['wallets']`
- Use `enabled` flag for conditional queries
- Zustand: UI state and offline/local data only — never API response data
- One store per feature domain; keep flat
- Persist: `expo-secure-store` for secrets, AsyncStorage for preferences
- 401 → trigger re-auth flow, not just a toast
- Never swallow errors (no empty catch); validate API response shape before use
